viz.option:
option = {
  xAxis: {
    type: 'category',
    data: ['Mon', 'Tue', 'Wed', 'Thu', 'Fri', 'Sat', 'Sun']
  },
  yAxis: {
    type: 'value'
  },
  series: [
    {
      data: [150, 230, 224, 218, 135, 147, 260],
      type: 'line'
    }
  ]
};

panel.html:

Customize your chart


      ECharts brings you thousands of different options to customize your chart. You can find the documentation here.
      We customize the chart by editing the option string. As mentioned the easiest way might be to use the ECharts example page as an IDE. 

      Let's add a title to our chart, give a name to the xAxis and yAxis, add a toolbox for switching between bar and linechart.
      To do this we only have to edit the option string.



Add the title:

  title: {
    text: "this is my first EChart in Splunk",
    left: "center",
    textStyle: {
      fontSize: 16
    },
  },

Name the xAxis and yAxis:

  xAxis: {
    type: 'category',
    data: ['Mon', 'Tue', 'Wed', 'Thu', 'Fri', 'Sat', 'Sun'],
    name: 'day of week'
  },
  yAxis: {
    type: 'value',
    name: 'pieces'
  },


Add the toolbox:

  toolbox: {
    show: true,
    feature: {
      magicType: {
        type: ["line", "bar"]
      },
      saveAsImage: {}
    }
  }


Which makes the final option string look like this:


    <option name="visualization_toolbox.hman.option">
option = {
  toolbox: {
    show: true,
    feature: {
      magicType: {
        type: ["line", "bar"]
      },
      saveAsImage: {}
    }
  },
  xAxis: {
    type: 'category',
    data: ['Mon', 'Tue', 'Wed', 'Thu', 'Fri', 'Sat', 'Sun'],
    name: 'day of week'
  },
  yAxis: {
    type: 'value',
    name: 'pieces'
  },
  title: {
    text: "this is my first EChart in Splunk",
    left: "center",
    textStyle: {
      fontSize: 16
    },
  },
  series: [
    {
      data: [150, 230, 224, 218, 135, 147, 260],
      type: 'bar'
    }
  ]
};

    </option>


You can also check the Source of this tutorial page. Checkout the chart below. Try to change the chart from bar to linechart by clicking on the toolbox icon in the top right corner of the chart.
You can also export the chart as an image by clicking on the save icon in the toolbox. Cool, right?!

viz.option:
option = {
  toolbox: {
    show: true,
    feature: {
      magicType: {
        type: ["line", "bar"]
      },
      saveAsImage: {}
    }
  },
  xAxis: {
    type: 'category',
    data: ['Mon', 'Tue', 'Wed', 'Thu', 'Fri', 'Sat', 'Sun'],
    name: 'day of week'
  },
  yAxis: {
    type: 'value',
    name: 'pieces'
  },
  title: {
    text: "this is my first EChart in Splunk",
    left: "center",
    textStyle: {
      fontSize: 16
    },
  },
  series: [
    {
      data: [150, 230, 224, 218, 135, 147, 260],
      type: 'bar'
    }
  ]
};
